content:
*   Orchestrate the containers. 
*   Deploy all the YAML files to GitHub.
*   Decide on the RESTful API endpoints to provide. 
*   Clean the CSV file to keep only the data we require to calculate our metrics and push the final data file to GitHub. 
*   Set up the Back end server and run it. 
*   Communicate with the Front end team to integrate our home page with the overall application. 
*   Come up with a test harness for all the tasks and deploy it to GitHub. All the tests will  be updated when written here. This acts as a single source of truth for our tests. 
*   Expose the API that might/might not do anything at this point, but can be implemented in future. 
*   Communicate with the Integration team on deploying our nascent containers and take part in the Integration testing. (One person can represent our team in the integration test.).
content_html:
• Orchestrate the containers. 
  • Deploy all the YAML files to GitHub.
  • Decide on the RESTful API endpoints to provide. 
  • Clean the CSV file to keep only the data we require to calculate our metrics and push the final data file to GitHub. 
  • Set up the Back end server and run it. 
  • Communicate with the Front end team to integrate our home page with the overall application. 
  • Come up with a test harness for all the tasks and deploy it to GitHub. All the tests will  be updated when written here. This acts as a single source of truth for our tests. 
  • Expose the API that might/might not do anything at this point, but can be implemented in future. 
  • Communicate with the Integration team on deploying our nascent containers and take part in the Integration testing. (One person can represent our team in the integration test.).

content:
**Sprint Retrospective:** 

Things that went well: 

*   Dividing teams based on micro services went well as the true spirit of micro services is to organize teams around business capabilities. 
*   Using Scrum of scrum board as the project level Information radiator went well. 

Things that did not go well: 

*   Having a separate Taiga integration team is of no use. 
*   Having a separate Integration team added waste into the process. 
*   Having many people in the group is becoming a challenge. 

Things to do in future sprints: 

*   Fetch your own data. 
*   Do TDD in all your tasks to meet the quality concerns of your project team. 
*   Perform catch up meetings with the Scrum of Scrums on a high level every alternate day for getting precise information.

content_diff:
* Orchestrate the containers. 
* Deploy all the YAML files to GitHub.
* Decide on the RESTful API endpoints to provide. 
* Clean the CSV file to keep only the data we require to calculate our metrics and push the final data file to GitHub. 
* Set up the Back end server and run it. 
* Communicate with the Front end team to integrate our home page with the overall application. 
* Come up with a test harness for all the tasks and deploy it to GitHub. All the tests will  be updated when written here. This acts as a single source of truth for our tests. 
* Expose the API that might/might not do anything at this point, but can be implemented in future. 
* Communicate with the Integration team on deploying our nascent containers and take part in the Integration testing. (One person can represent our team in the integration test.).
content_html:
• Orchestrate the containers. 
  • Deploy all the YAML files to GitHub.
  • Decide on the RESTful API endpoints to provide. 
  • Clean the CSV file to keep only the data we require to calculate our metrics and push the final data file to GitHub. 
  • Set up the Back end server and run it. 
  • Communicate with the Front end team to integrate our home page with the overall application. 
  • Come up with a test harness for all the tasks and deploy it to GitHub. All the tests will  be updated when written here. This acts as a single source of truth for our tests. 
  • Expose the API that might/might not do anything at this point, but can be implemented in future. 
  • Communicate with the Integration team on deploying our nascent containers and take part in the Integration testing. (One person can represent our team in the integration test.).

content_diff:
* **Initial YAML configuration set up for each of the tasks-** Impediment, CFD and WIP.
* Select the Taiga repository that has all the required data points to implement the services. 
* Decide on the back-end technology to go ahead with. 
* Decide on the API endpoints to expose. 
* Collaborate with the Integration team on a plan to integrate.
content_html:
• Initial YAML configuration set up for each of the tasks- Impediment, CFD and WIP.
  • Select the Taiga repository that has all the required data points to implement the services. 
  • Decide on the back-end technology to go ahead with. 
  • Decide on the API endpoints to expose. 
  • Collaborate with the Integration team on a plan to integrate.
